    {
      "id": "5d75d2a5-4a5b-4494-8d00-e6a8f53b7831",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Authors use data from learner discourse in FB groups and qureestionnaires, learner characteristics, and multiple latent variables related with distraction and engagement. Authors found that performance and perceived peer engagement were correlated. However, they also found that the use of ML to predict peer engagement generates features that are more predictive of performance than the self-reports.",
